In Ailao Mountains, southwest China's Yunnan Province, the valley of the tropical monsoon forest remains silent in the afternoon. A series of clucks breaks the silence. It is tea time for red junglefowl. Watch the video to learn more about the species. About 'Journeys in Nature': Ailao Mountains Series Sitting in the middle of southwest China's Yunnan Province, the Ailao Mountains are famous for their biodiversity. From endangered wild beasts like black crested gibbons and green peafowls to rare plants and various landscapes, the Ailao Mountains will never disappoint you. For more: Ailao Mountains Series | Ep. 5: Jiutian Wetland Ailao Mountains Series | Ep. 4: Flowering Cycas Ailao Mountains Series | Ep. 3: Neighbors in the mountains Ailao Mountains Series | Ep. 2: King of birds Ailao Mountains Series | Ep. 1: Phoenix at the river (Cover image a screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)